 <H1>Find sid’s of sailors who’ve reserved a red or a green boat</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>UNION: Can be used to compute the union of any two union-compatible sets of tuples (which are themselves the result of SQL queries).
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>If we replace OR by AND in the first version, what do we get?
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Also available:  EXCEPT  (What do we get if we replace UNION by EXCEPT?)</H2>
</UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  R.sid
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Boats B, Reserves R
</UL><UL>
WHERE  R.bid=B.bid
</UL><UL>
  AND (B.color=‘red’ OR B.color=‘green’)</UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  S.sid
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S, Boats B, Reserves R
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.sid=R.sid AND R.bid=B.bid
</UL><UL>
                AND B.color=‘red’
</UL><UL>
UNION
</UL><UL>
SELECT  S.sid
</UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S, Boats B, Reserves R
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.sid=R.sid AND R.bid=B.bid
</UL><UL>
                AND B.color=‘green’</UL></P>
